	2. Detect the args[1]. Like `$ cliCalc +` will run Tambah();

v2.0:
	1. Support x^2, 4^8, 4^x.
	2. Model:
		a. Programme ask user to input the square
		b. User input the value of square
		c. Programme ask user for will be squared number
		d. User inputs it
		e. Programme calculate result and print it
		f. Exit with status 0
